\f5\b0\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 Missing words & Missing some timestamps\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 The api will automaticly do text normalization on input text which may incorrectly remove or change some phrases. This can be disabled by adding\'a0
\f2\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 "normalization_options":\{"normalize": false\}
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0to your request json:\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
import requests\
\
response = requests.post(\
    "http://localhost:8880/v1/audio/speech",\
    json=\{\
        "input": "Hello world!",\
        "voice": "af_heart",\
        "response_format": "pcm",\
        "normalization_options":\
        \{\
            "normalize": False\
        \}\
    \},\
    stream=True\
)\
\
for chunk in response.iter_content(chunk_size=1024):\
    if chunk:\
        # Process streaming chunks\
        pass\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

