\f6\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Branching Strategy:
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f7\b\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 release
\f6\fs32 \'a0branch:
\f0\b0 \'a0Contains the latest stable build, recommended for production use. Docker images tagged with specific versions (e.g.,\'a0
\f2\fs27\fsmilli13600 v0.3.0
\f0\fs32 ) are built from this branch.\cb1 \
\ls5\ilvl0
\f7\b\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 master
\f6\fs32 \'a0branch:
\f0\b0 \'a0Used for active development. It may contain experimental features, ongoing changes, or fixes not yet in a stable release. Use this branch if you want the absolute latest code, but be aware it might be less stable. The\'a0
\f2\fs27\fsmilli13600 latest
\f0\fs32 \'a0Docker tag often points to builds from this branch.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Note: This is a\'a0
\f1\i \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 development
\f0\i0 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0focused project at its core.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 If you run into trouble, you may have to roll back a version on the release tags if something comes up, or build up from source and/or troubleshoot + submit a PR.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Free and open source is a community effort, and there's only really so many hours in a day. If you'd like to support the work, feel free to open a PR, buy me a coffee, or report any bugs/features/etc you find during use.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs24 \cf0 \strokec4 Linux GPU Permissions\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Some Linux users may encounter GPU permission issues when running as non-root. Can't guarantee anything, but here are some common solutions, consider your security requirements carefully\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f8\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Option 1: Container Groups (Likely the best option)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/remsky/Kokoro-FastAPI?tab=readme-ov-file#option-1-container-groups-likely-the-best-option"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b0\fs32 \cf2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf2 services:\
  kokoro-tts:\
    # ... existing config ...\
    group_add:\
      - "video"\
      - "render"\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f9\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f8\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Option 2: Host System Groups\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/remsky/Kokoro-FastAPI?tab=readme-ov-file#option-2-host-system-groups"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b0\fs32 \cf2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf2 services:\
  kokoro-tts:\
    # ... existing config ...\
    user: "$\{UID\}:$\{GID\}"\
    group_add:\
      - "video"\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f9\fs28 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Note: May require adding host user to groups:\'a0
\f2\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 sudo usermod -aG docker,video $USER
\f0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0and system restart.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f8\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Option 3: Device Permissions (Use with caution)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/remsky/Kokoro-FastAPI?tab=readme-ov-file#option-3-device-permissions-use-with-caution"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b0\fs32 \cf2 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cf2 services:\
  kokoro-tts:\
    # ... existing config ...\
    devices:\
      - /dev/nvidia0:/dev/nvidia0\
      - /dev/nvidiactl:/dev/nvidiactl\
      - /dev/nvidia-uvm:/dev/nvidia-uvm\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

